    "name": "Huaravito Reserve LTEMS",
    "lang": "en",
    "description": "The Huaravito Reserve Long-Term Ecological Monitoring Site (LTEMS) is an independent ecological monitoring initiative established within the Reserva Huaravito, Costa Rica. The site encompasses approximately 4,500 m² of mature secondary forest, locally known as Bosque Sagrado Toyopán, characterized by a high structural density of Hauya elegans (Guayabón), with an estimated 75–100 mature individuals concentrated within the western core sector. This initiative integrates microclimatic monitoring, forest structural assessment, and long-term biodiversity documentation into a unified data framework operating under the governance principles of the Sentinel Protocol.",
